entity.name: Boris Johnson is being challenged over his claim that 'no country has a working track and trace app'
entity.description: The prime minister was asked about the UK's abandoned track and trace app by Labour's Keir Starmer during Wednesday's Prime Minister's Questions. When Johnson asked Starmer to name a country with a function app, Starmer replied "Germany." Others have pointed out further countries that have launched apps.
